This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with training language models. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses different approaches to training neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the performance of RNNs. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the use of neural networks for language modeling. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it discusses the use of Target Propagation for training neural networks, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision.
